Document: VisualShaderNodeSmoothStep
Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodesmoothstep.rst
Summary: A shader node that interpolates input values between 0.0 and 1.0 using Hermite polynomials based on edge thresholds.

This node implements the smoothstep function, returning 0.0 when input x is below edge0, 1.0 when x exceeds edge1, and interpolated values between those thresholds. The interpolation uses Hermite polynomials to create smooth transitions. The function maps input values to a range between 0.0 and 1.0, making it useful for creating smooth transitions in shader graphs. The node operates by comparing the input value against two edge thresholds and calculating the interpolated result based on their relationship.
