Path: godot/classes/class_visualshadernodesmoothstep.rst
Summary: The op_type property defines the type of operands and returned value, with a default of 0.

OpType op_type = 0

Setter: set_op_type(value: OpType)
Getter: get_op_type() → OpType

The op_type property determines how the node handles input operands and output values. It uses the OpType enum which defines different operation modes. The default value is 0, which corresponds to the first enum variant. This property affects how the smooth step function is calculated between input values. The setter method allows changing the operation type, while the getter retrieves the current type. The specific behavior depends on the enum value assigned to this property.